President Biden has declared a state of emergency in Florida due to the Surfside Building Collapse that began on June 24, 2021. This declaration allows the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate disaster relief efforts to help the local population affected by the emergency. FEMA is authorized to provide equipment and resources as needed to alleviate the impacts of the emergency. Assistance for debris removal and emergency protective measures will also be provided. Thomas J. McCool has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.